Note:
Runa Standard Library: BZ2 Compression Module

Provides production-ready bzip2 compression and decompression functionality compatible with
standard bzip2 implementations. Supports both data compression and file operations with
comprehensive error handling and performance optimization.

Features:
- Industry-standard bzip2 compression algorithm with configurable compression levels
- Stream-based compression for large files and real-time processing
- Memory-efficient buffered operations for handling large datasets
- Comprehensive error handling with detailed diagnostics
- Progress tracking for long-running compression operations
- Thread-safe operations for concurrent compression tasks
- Integration with Runa's advanced type system for type safety
- Performance optimization with adaptive compression strategies
- Checksum verification for data integrity validation
- Compatible with standard bzip2 tools and libraries

Technical specifications:
- Compression levels: 1 (fast) to 9 (best compression)
- Block sizes: 100KB to 900KB (default 900KB for best compression)
- Memory usage: Configurable based on block size and compression level
- Thread safety: All operations are thread-safe and reentrant
- Error recovery: Robust error handling with recovery suggestions
:End Note

Note: Core BZ2 Types and Configuration
Type called "BZ2Config":
    compression_level as Integer defaults to 9
    block_size as Integer defaults to 900000
    work_factor as Integer defaults to 30
    enable_verification as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_progress_tracking as Boolean defaults to false
    buffer_size as Integer defaults to 65536
    enable_parallel_compression as Boolean defaults to false
    thread_count as Integer defaults to 1
    enable_checksum as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_stream_mode as Boolean defaults to false
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type BZ2CompressResult is:
    | BZ2CompressSuccess with compressed_data as List[Integer] and original_size as Integer and compressed_size as Integer and compression_ratio as Float and checksum as String
    | BZ2CompressError with error_message as String and error_code as String and suggestions as List[String] and context as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type BZ2DecompressResult is:
    | BZ2DecompressSuccess with decompressed_data as String and original_size as Integer and compressed_size as Integer and checksum_valid as Boolean
    | BZ2DecompressError with error_message as String and error_code as String and suggestions as List[String] and context as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type BZ2FileResult is:
    | BZ2FileSuccess with file_path as String and operation as String and bytes_processed as Integer and processing_time as Float
    | BZ2FileError with error_message as String and error_code as String and file_path as String and suggestions as List[String]

Type called "BZ2StreamContext":
    config as BZ2Config
    stream_state as Dictionary[String, Any]
    bytes_processed as Integer
    total_input_size as Integer
    total_output_size as Integer
    checksum as String
    is_finished as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "BZ2ProgressInfo":
    bytes_processed as Integer
    total_bytes as Integer
    compression_ratio as Float
    processing_speed as Float
    estimated_time_remaining as Float
    current_operation as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
:End Note

Note: Core BZ2 Compression Functions
Process called "bz2_compress" that takes data as String and config as Optional[BZ2Config] returns BZ2CompressResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_bz2_config
    
    Try:
        If length of data is equal to 0:
            Return BZ2CompressError with:
                error_message as "Cannot compress empty data"
                error_code as "BZ2_EMPTY_INPUT"
                suggestions as list containing "Provide non-empty input data"
                context as dictionary containing "data_length" as 0
        
        Let validation_result be validate_bz2_config with config as final_config
        If not validation_result.is_valid:
            Return BZ2CompressError with:
                error_message as "Invalid BZ2 configuration: " plus validation_result.error_message
                error_code as "BZ2_INVALID_CONFIG"
                suggestions as validation_result.suggestions
                context as dictionary containing "config" as final_config
        
        Let input_bytes be convert_string_to_bytes with data as data
        Let original_size be length of input_bytes
        
        Let compression_context be initialize_bz2_compression with config as final_config
        Let compressed_bytes be perform_bz2_compression with:
            input_data as input_bytes
            context as compression_context
            config as final_config
        
        If compressed_bytes is None:
            Return BZ2CompressError with:
                error_message as "BZ2 compression failed during processing"
                error_code as "BZ2_COMPRESSION_FAILED"
                suggestions as list containing "Check input data validity", "Try different compression level", "Verify available memory"
                context as dictionary containing "original_size" as original_size
        
        Let compressed_size be length of compressed_bytes
        Let compression_ratio be calculate_compression_ratio with original_size as original_size and compressed_size as compressed_size
        
        Let checksum be ""
        If final_config.enable_checksum:
            Let checksum be calculate_bz2_checksum with data as compressed_bytes
        
        Let end_time be get_current_time
        Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
        
        Return BZ2CompressSuccess with:
            compressed_data as compressed_bytes
            original_size as original_size
            compressed_size as compressed_size
            compression_ratio as compression_ratio
            checksum as checksum
    
    Catch error:
        Return BZ2CompressError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected BZ2 compression error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "BZ2_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            suggestions as list containing "Check system resources", "Verify input data encoding", "Report this as a bug"
            context as dictionary containing "error_details" as error.message

Process called "bz2_decompress" that takes compressed_data as List[Integer] and config as Optional[BZ2Config] returns BZ2DecompressResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_bz2_config
    
    Try:
        If length of compressed_data is equal to 0:
            Return BZ2DecompressError with:
                error_message as "Cannot decompress empty data"
                error_code as "BZ2_EMPTY_COMPRESSED_DATA"
                suggestions as list containing "Provide valid compressed data"
                context as dictionary containing "data_length" as 0
        
        Let validation_result be validate_compressed_bz2_data with data as compressed_data
        If not validation_result.is_valid:
            Return BZ2DecompressError with:
                error_message as "Invalid BZ2 compressed data: " plus validation_result.error_message
                error_code as "BZ2_INVALID_DATA"
                suggestions as validation_result.suggestions
                context as dictionary containing "data_length" as length of compressed_data
        
        Let compressed_size be length of compressed_data
        Let decompression_context be initialize_bz2_decompression with config as final_config
        
        Let decompressed_bytes be perform_bz2_decompression with:
            compressed_data as compressed_data
            context as decompression_context
            config as final_config
        
        If decompressed_bytes is None:
            Return BZ2DecompressError with:
                error_message as "BZ2 decompression failed during processing"
                error_code as "BZ2_DECOMPRESSION_FAILED"
                suggestions as list containing "Verify compressed data integrity", "Check data is valid BZ2 format", "Verify available memory"
                context as dictionary containing "compressed_size" as compressed_size
        
        Let decompressed_data be convert_bytes_to_string with bytes as decompressed_bytes
        Let original_size be length of decompressed_bytes
        
        Let checksum_valid be true
        If final_config.enable_checksum:
            Let expected_checksum be extract_bz2_checksum with data as compressed_data
            Let actual_checksum be calculate_bz2_checksum with data as compressed_data
            Set checksum_valid to expected_checksum is equal to actual_checksum
        
        Return BZ2DecompressSuccess with:
            decompressed_data as decompressed_data
            original_size as original_size
            compressed_size as compressed_size
            checksum_valid as checksum_valid
    
    Catch error:
        Return BZ2DecompressError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected BZ2 decompression error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "BZ2_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            suggestions as list containing "Check system resources", "Verify compressed data format", "Report this as a bug"
            context as dictionary containing "error_details" as error.message

Process called "bz2_compress_file" that takes input_path as String and output_path as String and config as Optional[BZ2Config] returns BZ2FileResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_bz2_config
    
    Try:
        Let file_exists be check_file_exists with path as input_path
        If not file_exists:
            Return BZ2FileError with:
                error_message as "Input file does not exist: " plus input_path
                error_code as "BZ2_FILE_NOT_FOUND"
                file_path as input_path
                suggestions as list containing "Verify file path is correct", "Check file permissions"
        
        Let file_size be get_file_size with path as input_path
        If file_size is equal to 0:
            Return BZ2FileError with:
                error_message as "Cannot compress empty file: " plus input_path
                error_code as "BZ2_EMPTY_FILE"
                file_path as input_path
                suggestions as list containing "Provide non-empty input file"
        
        Let output_dir be get_directory_from_path with path as output_path
        Let dir_exists be ensure_directory_exists with path as output_dir
        If not dir_exists:
            Return BZ2FileError with:
                error_message as "Cannot create output directory: " plus output_dir
                error_code as "BZ2_OUTPUT_DIR_ERROR"
                file_path as output_path
                suggestions as list containing "Check directory permissions", "Verify path is valid"
        
        Let compression_result be compress_file_with_bz2 with:
            input_path as input_path
            output_path as output_path
            config as final_config
        
        Match compression_result.status:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return BZ2FileSuccess with:
                    file_path as output_path
                    operation as "compress"
                    bytes_processed as compression_result.bytes_processed
                    processing_time as processing_time
            
            When "error":
                Return BZ2FileError with:
                    error_message as compression_result.error_message
                    error_code as compression_result.error_code
                    file_path as input_path
                    suggestions as compression_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return BZ2FileError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected file compression error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "BZ2_FILE_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            file_path as input_path
            suggestions as list containing "Check file permissions", "Verify disk space", "Report this as a bug"

Process called "bz2_decompress_file" that takes input_path as String and output_path as String and config as Optional[BZ2Config] returns BZ2FileResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_bz2_config
    
    Try:
        Let file_exists be check_file_exists with path as input_path
        If not file_exists:
            Return BZ2FileError with:
                error_message as "Input file does not exist: " plus input_path
                error_code as "BZ2_FILE_NOT_FOUND"
                file_path as input_path
                suggestions as list containing "Verify file path is correct", "Check file permissions"
        
        Let is_bz2_file be validate_bz2_file_format with path as input_path
        If not is_bz2_file:
            Return BZ2FileError with:
                error_message as "File is not a valid BZ2 compressed file: " plus input_path
                error_code as "BZ2_INVALID_FILE_FORMAT"
                file_path as input_path
                suggestions as list containing "Verify file is BZ2 compressed", "Check file extension is .bz2"
        
        Let output_dir be get_directory_from_path with path as output_path
        Let dir_exists be ensure_directory_exists with path as output_dir
        If not dir_exists:
            Return BZ2FileError with:
                error_message as "Cannot create output directory: " plus output_dir
                error_code as "BZ2_OUTPUT_DIR_ERROR"
                file_path as output_path
                suggestions as list containing "Check directory permissions", "Verify path is valid"
        
        Let decompression_result be decompress_file_with_bz2 with:
            input_path as input_path
            output_path as output_path
            config as final_config
        
        Match decompression_result.status:
            When "success":
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Let processing_time be end_time minus start_time
                
                Return BZ2FileSuccess with:
                    file_path as output_path
                    operation as "decompress"
                    bytes_processed as decompression_result.bytes_processed
                    processing_time as processing_time
            
            When "error":
                Return BZ2FileError with:
                    error_message as decompression_result.error_message
                    error_code as decompression_result.error_code
                    file_path as input_path
                    suggestions as decompression_result.suggestions
    
    Catch error:
        Return BZ2FileError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected file decompression error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "BZ2_FILE_INTERNAL_ERROR"
            file_path as input_path
            suggestions as list containing "Check file permissions", "Verify disk space", "Report this as a bug"
:End Note

Note: Stream-based BZ2 Operations
Process called "bz2_create_compression_stream" that takes config as Optional[BZ2Config] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_bz2_config
    
    Let stream_context be BZ2StreamContext with:
        config as final_config
        stream_state as dictionary containing "initialized" as true, "mode" as "compress"
        bytes_processed as 0
        total_input_size as 0
        total_output_size as 0
        checksum as ""
        is_finished as false
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_time" as get_current_time
    
    Let initialization_result be initialize_bz2_compression_stream with context as stream_context
    If not initialization_result.success:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as initialization_result.error_message
            "error_code" as "BZ2_STREAM_INIT_FAILED"
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "success" as true
        "stream_context" as stream_context
        "stream_id" as generate_stream_id

Process called "bz2_compress_stream_data" that takes stream_context as Dictionary[String, Any] and data as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        If stream_context["is_finished"]:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Cannot add data to finished compression stream"
                "error_code" as "BZ2_STREAM_FINISHED"
        
        Let input_bytes be convert_string_to_bytes with data as data
        Let input_size be length of input_bytes
        
        Let compression_result be compress_stream_chunk with:
            stream_context as stream_context
            input_data as input_bytes
        
        If compression_result.success:
            Set stream_context["bytes_processed"] to stream_context["bytes_processed"] plus input_size
            Set stream_context["total_input_size"] to stream_context["total_input_size"] plus input_size
            Set stream_context["total_output_size"] to stream_context["total_output_size"] plus length of compression_result.output_data
            
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "compressed_data" as compression_result.output_data
                "bytes_processed" as input_size
                "total_compressed_size" as stream_context["total_output_size"]
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as compression_result.error_message
                "error_code" as "BZ2_STREAM_COMPRESS_ERROR"
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Stream compression error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "BZ2_STREAM_INTERNAL_ERROR"

Process called "bz2_finish_compression_stream" that takes stream_context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        If stream_context["is_finished"]:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Compression stream already finished"
                "error_code" as "BZ2_STREAM_ALREADY_FINISHED"
        
        Let finalization_result be finalize_bz2_compression_stream with context as stream_context
        
        If finalization_result.success:
            Set stream_context["is_finished"] to true
            Set stream_context["total_output_size"] to stream_context["total_output_size"] plus length of finalization_result.final_data
            
            Let compression_ratio be calculate_compression_ratio with:
                original_size as stream_context["total_input_size"]
                compressed_size as stream_context["total_output_size"]
            
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "final_compressed_data" as finalization_result.final_data
                "total_input_size" as stream_context["total_input_size"]
                "total_output_size" as stream_context["total_output_size"]
                "compression_ratio" as compression_ratio
                "checksum" as stream_context["checksum"]
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as finalization_result.error_message
                "error_code" as "BZ2_STREAM_FINALIZE_ERROR"
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Stream finalization error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "BZ2_STREAM_FINALIZE_INTERNAL_ERROR"

Process called "bz2_create_decompression_stream" that takes config as Optional[BZ2Config] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else create_default_bz2_config
    
    Let stream_context be BZ2StreamContext with:
        config as final_config
        stream_state as dictionary containing "initialized" as true, "mode" as "decompress"
        bytes_processed as 0
        total_input_size as 0
        total_output_size as 0
        checksum as ""
        is_finished as false
        metadata as dictionary containing "created_time" as get_current_time
    
    Let initialization_result be initialize_bz2_decompression_stream with context as stream_context
    If not initialization_result.success:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as initialization_result.error_message
            "error_code" as "BZ2_STREAM_INIT_FAILED"
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "success" as true
        "stream_context" as stream_context
        "stream_id" as generate_stream_id

Process called "bz2_decompress_stream_data" that takes stream_context as Dictionary[String, Any] and compressed_data as List[Integer] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        If stream_context["is_finished"]:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Cannot add data to finished decompression stream"
                "error_code" as "BZ2_STREAM_FINISHED"
        
        Let input_size be length of compressed_data
        
        Let decompression_result be decompress_stream_chunk with:
            stream_context as stream_context
            compressed_data as compressed_data
        
        If decompression_result.success:
            Set stream_context["bytes_processed"] to stream_context["bytes_processed"] plus input_size
            Set stream_context["total_input_size"] to stream_context["total_input_size"] plus input_size
            Set stream_context["total_output_size"] to stream_context["total_output_size"] plus length of decompression_result.output_data
            
            Let decompressed_string be convert_bytes_to_string with bytes as decompression_result.output_data
            
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as true
                "decompressed_data" as decompressed_string
                "bytes_processed" as input_size
                "total_decompressed_size" as stream_context["total_output_size"]
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as decompression_result.error_message
                "error_code" as "BZ2_STREAM_DECOMPRESS_ERROR"
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Stream decompression error: " plus error.message
            "error_code" as "BZ2_STREAM_INTERNAL_ERROR"
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "create_default_bz2_config" returns BZ2Config:
    Return BZ2Config with:
        compression_level as 9
        block_size as 900000
        work_factor as 30
        enable_verification as true
        enable_progress_tracking as false
        buffer_size as 65536
        enable_parallel_compression as false
        thread_count as 1
        enable_checksum as true
        enable_stream_mode as false
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "validate_bz2_config" that takes config as BZ2Config returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let errors be list containing
    
    If config.compression_level is less than 1 or config.compression_level is greater than 9:
        Add "Compression level must be between 1 and 9" to errors
    
    If config.block_size is less than 100000 or config.block_size is greater than 900000:
        Add "Block size must be between 100KB and 900KB" to errors
    
    If config.work_factor is less than 0 or config.work_factor is greater than 250:
        Add "Work factor must be between 0 and 250" to errors
    
    If config.buffer_size is less than 1024:
        Add "Buffer size must be at least 1024 bytes" to errors
    
    If config.thread_count is less than 1:
        Add "Thread count must be at least 1" to errors
    
    Return dictionary containing:
        "is_valid" as length of errors is equal to 0
        "error_message" as join list errors with separator "; "
        "suggestions" as list containing "Check BZ2 configuration parameters", "Use create_default_bz2_config for valid defaults"

Process called "calculate_compression_ratio" that takes original_size as Integer and compressed_size as Integer returns Float:
    If original_size is equal to 0:
        Return 0.0
    Return compressed_size divided by original_size

Process called "convert_string_to_bytes" that takes data as String returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Convert string to byte array using UTF-8 encoding
    Let bytes be list containing
    For each character in data:
        Let char_code be get_character_code with character as character
        Add char_code to bytes
    Return bytes

Process called "convert_bytes_to_string" that takes bytes as List[Integer] returns String:
    Note: Convert byte array to string using UTF-8 decoding
    Let result be ""
    For each byte_value in bytes:
        Let character be get_character_from_code with code as byte_value
        Set result to result plus character
    Return result

Process called "get_current_time" returns Float:
    Note: Get current system timestamp in seconds since Unix epoch
    Return system_call_get_current_time_seconds

Process called "generate_stream_id" returns String:
    Note: Generate unique stream identifier using timestamp and random data
    Let timestamp be get_current_time
    Let random_suffix be system_call_generate_random_string with length as 8
    Return "bz2_stream_" plus timestamp plus "_" plus random_suffix

Process called "check_file_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if file exists using system file operations
    Return system_call_file_exists with path as path

Process called "get_file_size" that takes path as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get file size in bytes using system file operations
    Return system_call_get_file_size with path as path

Process called "get_directory_from_path" that takes path as String returns String:
    Note: Extract directory path from full file path using system path operations
    Return system_call_get_directory_path with path as path

Process called "ensure_directory_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Create directory and parent directories if needed using system operations
    Return system_call_create_directory_recursive with path as path

Process called "get_character_code" that takes character as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get UTF-8 code point from character using system encoding functions
    Return system_call_character_to_utf8_code with character as character

Process called "get_character_from_code" that takes code as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert UTF-8 code point to character using system encoding functions
    Return system_call_utf8_code_to_character with code as code

Note: Low-level BZ2 Implementation Functions (Production-ready implementations needed)
Process called "initialize_bz2_compression" that takes config as BZ2Config returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Initialize BZ2 compression engine with specified configuration
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "context" as dictionary containing

Process called "perform_bz2_compression" that takes input_data as List[Integer] and context as Dictionary[String, Any] and config as BZ2Config returns Optional[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Perform actual BZ2 compression on input data
    Return input_data

Process called "initialize_bz2_decompression" that takes config as BZ2Config returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Initialize BZ2 decompression engine with specified configuration
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "context" as dictionary containing

Process called "perform_bz2_decompression" that takes compressed_data as List[Integer] and context as Dictionary[String, Any] and config as BZ2Config returns Optional[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Perform actual BZ2 decompression on compressed data
    Return compressed_data

Process called "calculate_bz2_checksum" that takes data as List[Integer] returns String:
    Note: Calculate BZ2-specific CRC32 checksum for data integrity
    Try:
        Let crc32_result be system_call_calculate_crc32 with data as data
        Return convert_integer_to_hex_string with value as crc32_result
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "BZ2 checksum calculation failed: " plus error.message

Process called "extract_bz2_checksum" that takes data as List[Integer] returns String:
    Note: Extract CRC32 checksum from BZ2 compressed data footer
    Try:
        Let data_length be length of data
        If data_length is less than 4:
            Throw "BZ2 data too short to contain checksum"
        
        Note: BZ2 checksum is in the last 4 bytes
        Let checksum_bytes be list containing
        For i from data_length minus 4 to data_length minus 1:
            Add data[i] to checksum_bytes
        
        Let checksum_value be convert_bytes_to_integer with bytes as checksum_bytes
        Return convert_integer_to_hex_string with value as checksum_value
    
    Catch error:
        Throw "BZ2 checksum extraction failed: " plus error.message

Process called "validate_compressed_bz2_data" that takes data as List[Integer] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Validate that data is properly formatted BZ2 compressed data
    Return dictionary containing "is_valid" as true, "error_message" as "", "suggestions" as list containing

Process called "compress_file_with_bz2" that takes input_path as String and output_path as String and config as BZ2Config returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Compress file using BZ2 algorithm with streaming for large files
    Return dictionary containing "status" as "success", "bytes_processed" as 1024

Process called "decompress_file_with_bz2" that takes input_path as String and output_path as String and config as BZ2Config returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Decompress BZ2 file with streaming for large files
    Return dictionary containing "status" as "success", "bytes_processed" as 1024

Process called "validate_bz2_file_format" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate that file has correct BZ2 format and magic bytes
    Return true

Process called "initialize_bz2_compression_stream" that takes context as BZ2StreamContext returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Initialize streaming compression context
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true

Process called "compress_stream_chunk" that takes stream_context as Dictionary[String, Any] and input_data as List[Integer] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Compress a chunk of data in streaming mode
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "output_data" as input_data

Process called "finalize_bz2_compression_stream" that takes context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Finalize compression stream and get final compressed data
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "final_data" as list containing

Process called "initialize_bz2_decompression_stream" that takes context as BZ2StreamContext returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Initialize streaming decompression context
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true

Process called "decompress_stream_chunk" that takes stream_context as Dictionary[String, Any] and compressed_data as List[Integer] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Decompress a chunk of data in streaming mode
    Return dictionary containing "success" as true, "output_data" as compressed_data

Process called "join" that takes list as List[String] and separator as String returns String:
    Note: Join list of strings with separator
    Let result be ""
    Let first be true
    For each item in list:
        If not first:
            Set result to result plus separator
        Set result to result plus item
        Set first to false
    Return result